       <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>The Learning Management System (eflow) API is designed to help institutions manage courses, students, attendance, assessments, and reports efficiently. This documentation provides a detailed guide on how to interact with the eflow API.</p>

    <h2>Authentication</h2>
    <p>All API requests must include an authentication token in the header.</p>
    <pre><code>{ "Authorization": "Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN" }</code></pre>

    <h2>Base URL</h2>
    <pre><code>https://api.youreflow.com/v1</code></pre>

    <h2>Endpoints</h2>

    <h3>1. User Management</h3>
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h4>Register a User</h4>
        <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST | <strong>Endpoint:</strong> /users/register</p>
        <pre><code>{ "name": "John Doe", "email": "johndoe@example.com", "password": "password123" }</code></pre>
        <pre><code>{ "message": "User registered successfully", "userId": "12345" }</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="endpoint">
        <h4>User Login</h4>
        <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST | <strong>Endpoint:</strong> /users/login</p>
        <pre><code>{ "email": "johndoe@example.com", "password": "password123" }</code></pre>
        <pre><code>{ "token": "your_jwt_token" }</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h3>2. Institute Management</h3>
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h4>Create an Institute</h4>
        <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST | <strong>Endpoint:</strong> /institutes</p>
        <pre><code>{ "name": "XYZ Institute", "address": "123 Main Street", "contact": "9876543210" }</code></pre>
        <pre><code>{ "message": "Institute created successfully", "instituteId": "67890" }</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h3>3. Course Management</h3>
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h4>Create a Course</h4>
        <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST | <strong>Endpoint:</strong> /courses</p>
        <pre><code>{ "name": "Java Programming", "description": "Introduction to Java", "instituteId": "67890" }</code></pre>
        <pre><code>{ "message": "Course created successfully", "courseId": "445566" }</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h3>4. Student Management</h3>
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h4>Add a Student</h4>
        <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST | <strong>Endpoint:</strong> /students</p>
        <pre><code>{ "name": "Alice Smith", "email": "alice@example.com", "instituteId": "67890" }</code></pre>
        <pre><code>{ "message": "Student added successfully", "studentId": "112233" }</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h3>5. Attendance Management</h3>
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h4>Mark Attendance</h4>
        <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST | <strong>Endpoint:</strong> /attendance</p>
        <pre><code>{ "studentId": "112233", "date": "2025-01-31", "status": "Present" }</code></pre>
        <pre><code>{ "message": "Attendance marked successfully" }</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h3>6. Report Generation</h3>
    <div class="endpoint">
        <h4>Generate Student Report</h4>
        <p><strong>Method:</strong> GET | <strong>Endpoint:</strong> /reports/student/112233</p>
        <pre><code>{ "studentId": "112233", "attendance": "95%", "grades": "A" }</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2>Error Handling</h2>
    <p>All API responses include a status code indicating success or failure.</p>
    <pre><code>{ "error": "Invalid credentials" }</code></pre>
</div> 
